JDK 7 (OpenJDK):

Note that this is for pre-release builds.
For post-release updates, see https://jdk7.java.net/source.html

For compilation, I should just install the JSR 308 compiler instead.
(But, that's just the compiler, not all of OpenJDK.)

Two techniques: mercurial or download

----------------

## Mercurial (for source code):
# No need to do this; my other instructions made a ~/java/openjdk8/.

----------------

## Note that this may intermittently fail, especially on a Thursday when
## Oracle is updating the weekly build.

# On 1/8/2009 at CSE, running this yielded an installation that didn't seem
# to work for me.  In particular, running
#   java -jar $inv/java/lookup.jar
# yielded
#   Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: com/sun/javadoc/RootDoc
# even though tools.jar was on the classpath.  Switching the symbolic link
# back to JDK6 permitted me to run the program.

## Download:
# See http://download.java.net/openjdk/jdk7/ to set these environment variables.
export OJDKBUILDNO="b147"
export OJDKDATE="27_jun_2011"
# export EA="ea"
export EA="fcs"
export OJDKVERSION=${OJDKBUILDNO}-linux-i586-${OJDKDATE}
export JDKPARENTDIR=$HOME/java/
mkdir -p $JDKPARENTDIR
cd $JDKPARENTDIR
rm -f jdk1.7.0
# wget http://www.java.net/download/jdk7/archive/${OJDKBUILDNO}/binaries/jdk-7-${EA}-bin-b137-linux-i586-07_apr_2011.tar.gz
# chmod +x jdk-7-${EA}-bin-${OJDKVERSION}.bin
# # "yes |" mostly works, but one bit of user interaction is required by "more".
# yes | ./jdk-7-${EA}-bin-${OJDKVERSION}.bin
# wget http://download.java.net/jdk7/binaries/jdk-7-ea-bin-${OJDKVERSION}.tar.gz
wget http://www.java.net/download/jdk7/archive/${OJDKBUILDNO}/binaries/jdk-7-${EA}-bin-${OJDKVERSION}.tar.gz
tar xzf jdk-7-${EA}-bin-${OJDKVERSION}.tar.gz
mv jdk1.7.0 jdk1.7.0-${OJDKBUILDNO}
ln -s jdk1.7.0-${OJDKBUILDNO} jdk1.7.0
rm -f jdk
ln -s jdk1.7.0 jdk
mkdir jdk/src
# This src.zip file contains files that are not in the source bundle nor in
# the repository at http://hg.openjdk.java.net/jdk7/jdk7, for example
# java.io.FileDescriptor.  (Why?)
(cd jdk/src; unzip ../src.zip)

### JDK 7 docs
export JDKDOCDIR=$HOME/java/jdk1.7.0
cd $JDKDOCDIR
# wget http://www.java.net/download/jdk7/jdk-7-${EA}-bin-$OJDKBUILDNO-apidocs-$OJDKDATE.jar
# # This java command pops up a GUI.  Answer question: install in $HOME/java/jdk1.7.0
# java -jar jdk-7-${EA}-bin-$OJDKBUILDNO-apidocs-$OJDKDATE.jar
wget http://www.java.net/download/jdk7/archive/$OJDKBUILDNO/jdk-7-${EA}-bin-$OJDKBUILDNO-apidocs-$OJDKDATE.zip
unzip jdk-7-${EA}-bin-$OJDKBUILDNO-apidocs-$OJDKDATE.zip
# Only necessary once ever: cd ~/java; ln -s jdk/docs_www jdk-docs; ln -s jdk1.7.0 jdk7
javadoc-index-to-alist > ~/.javadoc-index.el

### JDK 7 docs
export JDKDOCDIR=$HOME/java/jdk1.7.0
cd $JDKDOCDIR
# wget http://www.java.net/download/jdk7/jdk-7-${EA}-bin-$OJDKBUILDNO-apidocs-$OJDKDATE.jar
# # This java command pops up a GUI.  Answer question: install in $HOME/java/jdk1.7.0
# java -jar jdk-7-${EA}-bin-$OJDKBUILDNO-apidocs-$OJDKDATE.jar
wget http://www.java.net/download/jdk7/archive/$OJDKBUILDNO/jdk-7-${EA}-bin-$OJDKBUILDNO-apidocs-$OJDKDATE.zip
unzip jdk-7-${EA}-bin-$OJDKBUILDNO-apidocs-$OJDKDATE.zip
# Only necessary once ever: cd ~/java; ln -s jdk/docs_www jdk-docs; ln -s jdk1.7.0 jdk7
javadoc-index-to-alist > ~/.javadoc-index.el

