JDK 6:

From 
  http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javasebusiness/downloads/java-archive-downloads-javase6-419409.html#jdk-6u43-oth-JPR
download
  jdk-6u43-linux-x64.bin
mv ~/tmp/jdk-6u43-linux-x64.bin ~/java
cd ~/java
chmod +x jdk-6u43-linux-x64.bin
./jdk-6u43-linux-x64.bin
ln -s jdk1.6.0_43 jdk6

===========================================================================

JDK 6 for Linux:

----------------

# Follow the instructions at
#   http://ubuntuguide.org/wiki/Ubuntu_Edgy#How_to_install_Java_Development_Kit_.28JDK.29_v5.0
# but modify for Java 6 as follows.

# 1. First, download jdk-6-doc.zip from http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/
# and put it in /tmp, owned by root.root.

# 2. Run the following commands.
sudo apt install sun-java6-bin sun-java6-demo sun-java6-doc sun-java6-fonts sun-java6-jdk sun-java6-jre sun-java6-plugin sun-java6-source
sudo update-java-alternatives -s java-6-sun
# Add /usr/lib/jvm/java-6-sun to the top of /etc/jvm
sudo emacs /etc/jvm
# I didn't do the fonts_backup fix yet, though.

# The source (from sun-java6-source) is in
#   /usr/lib/jvm/java-6-sun-1.6.0.05/src.zip
# and documentation only in
#   /usr/share/doc/sun-java6-source


===========================================================================

# My personal setup:

# Java 6 (on Ubuntu)
mkdir -p ~/java
cd ~/java
rm -f jdk6
ln -s /usr/lib/jvm/java-6-sun jdk6
rm -f jdk1.6
ln -s /usr/lib/jvm/java-6-sun jdk1.6

## Watch out!  This is too many levels of symbolic links...
# mkdir -p ~/java
# ln -s /usr/lib/jvm/java-6-sun jdk1.6.0
# rm -f jdk1.6
# ln -s jdk1.6.0 jdk1.6
# rm -f jdk6
# ln -s jdk1.6 jdk6
# rm -f jdk
# ln -s jdk6 jdk


